<HEADLINE>
PRAYER COMES FIRST, BUT FOOTBALL GAME IS THE MAIN EVENT 
</HEADLINE>
   By DIRK JOHNSON   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   SANTA FE, Texas _ Despite talk of a huge rally of prayer and
protest, it was cheers for the boys in cleats that took center
stage Friday night under the lights at the high school football
field here.
</P>
<P>
   Many fans quietly recited The Lord's Prayer before the start of
the game, an action designed partly to protest the Supreme Court
ruling in June that forbade a pre-game prayer routine led by
students. But most of the noise came from clapping hands and shouts
for the young football players.
</P>
<P>
   ``The crowd is much, much, much smaller than we had feared it
would be,'' said Gary Causey, the principal at Santa Fe High
