   But Candy Gerulis, a 43-year-old hair stylist from Santa Fe, was
one who said the scene bothered her.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is crazy,'' said Gerulis, who was raised Catholic. ``It
makes me feel uncomfortable to have people stand up and start
praying around me at a football game.''
</P>
<P>
   The game Friday night _ between the Santa Fe Indians and the
Hitchcock Bulldogs, which Santa Fe won 21-14 _ was the first in
town after the the Supreme Court ruling that prohibited the
pre-game prayers led by students in a ritual that amounted to an
official ceremony.
</P>
<P>
   The 6-3 majority opinion by Jus- tice John Paul Stevens said
that even when attendance at a game was vol- untary and even when
