<P>
   EUROPE-THEME-PARKS (Dronten, the Netherlands) _ Europeans
visited amusement parks in record numbers this summer, stirred by
spreading affluence, booming tourism and greater variety. In the
last decade the number of theme parks in Europe has increased by a
third, while the number of admissions has risen two-thirds, and
revenues doubled to $2.2 billion. The expansion is gathering
momentum and drawing outside investment, notably from the United
States, transforming the European industry, long known for
family-owned mom-and-pop parks.
</P>
