<SLUG> BC-CHEERLEADING-TEXT-REVIEW-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WHERE A TEENAGER GIVES ORDERS 
</HEADLINE>
   (The Week in Review)  
 (NOTE TO INTERNATIONAL CLIENTS: For international clients' use by
special arrangement only. Asian and European points: contact Karl
Horwitz in Paris for details and prices (Phone: 47 42 17 11; FAX:
47-42-80-44). Latin American points: contact the Los Angeles office
(Phone: 310-996-0075; FAX: 310-996-0089)  
 (editors: text that should be italicized is marked with (BEGIN
ITALICS HERE) and (END ITALICS HERE)  
 By JOE SHARKEY   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Football season is here again, and as anyone who has been to a
high school or college game in recent years knows, this is not your
Aunt Gidget's cheerleading squad anymore. Today's cheerleaders
tumble, vault, build human pyramids _ and sometimes exhibit higher
