issue orders to recall and repair the vehicles. Analysts estimated
the cost could run as high as $250 million.
</P>
<P>
   Ford refuted the finding, and predicted it would be reversed on
appeal.
</P>
<P>
   A New Trial for American
</P>
<P>
   After an election marred by charges of voter fraud, President
Alberto K. Fujimori of Peru no doubt needs all the friends he can
get. That could well explain Peru's decision to grant a new trial
