<DOCNO> NYT20000902.0048 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-02 10:28 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A6250 &Cx1f; var-z
u i BC-SUBMARINES-REVIEW-NYT     09-02 0616
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SUBMARINES-REVIEW-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SUBMARINES AND THE HIDDEN COSTS OF CLOAK AND DAGGER 
</HEADLINE>
   (The Week in Review)  
 (NOTE TO INTERNATIONAL CLIENTS: For international clients' use by
special arrangement only. Asian and European points: contact Karl
Horwitz in Paris for details and prices (Phone: 47 42 17 11; FAX:
47-42-80-44). Latin American points: contact the Los Angeles office
(Phone: 310-996-0075; FAX: 310-996-0089)  
 By CHRISTOPHER DREW   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Before the nuclear-powered attack submarine USS Memphis embarked
on a recent spy mission _ in which, Navy officials have said, it
captured the sounds of the explosions that helped sink Russia's
Kursk submarine last month _ one unsettling precaution was taken. A
