<P>
   ELDERLY-DRIVERS (Los Angeles) _ The case of the 91-year-old
motorist who backed into a bank and killed an infant last week has
sparked intense debate among the elderly, who say they should be
allow to drive if they pass tests like everyone else. By Dennis
McCarthy. (Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California
news files.)
</P>
<P>
   PEST-PASTRY (Los Angeles) _ In the latest assault on the
eucalyptus tree-crippling red gum lerp psyllid, a naturalist
insists that making a tasty snack of the insects and their
excretions will help. ``Classifying the lerp psyllid as a problem
is a matter of perspective,'' said Christopher Nyerges, a Los
Angles resident who has taught natural food and survival classes
for more than two decades. By Dominic Berbeo. (Will move in the
``a'' national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   CALIF-SESQ (Los Angeles) _ California's 150th anniversary of
statehood is Sept. 9, but who knew? The number of Golden State
residents aware of it is nearly as low as the number who can define
``sesquicentennial.'' Festivities -- planned for Labor Day through
Saturday -- have drawn little notice since the state's troubled
sesquicentennial commission disbanded last year amid complaints
abouts its failures, lack of support and finger-pointing. By Alexa
Haussler. (Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California
news files.)
