<SLUG> BC-NASCAR-ADV0903-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Burtons going for a sweep
 &HT;    By Michael Carvell
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DARLINGTON, S.C. _ Ward and Jeff Burton have been coming to the
Southern 500 since their parents brought them to Darlington Raceway
as children.
</P>
<P>
   ``I used to camp near the track and attend the races there with
my father, brothers and friends when I was younger,'' Ward said.
``It is a very special track, one with a lot of history and one of
the last of its type left on our circuit.''
</P>
<P>
   The Burton brothers have created their own history at ``The
Track Too Tough To Tame'' during the past two seasons. Jeff
captured both of the rain-shortened events in 1999. Ward, who won
the Mall.com 400 in March, will go for another Burton sweep in
today's 1 p.m. race.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think the main thing is we just need to stay real focused
and get a competitive finish out of it,'' Ward said. ``Whether
we're going to have the car to win or not, we've got 450 miles to
get to that point and then we'll decide like we do every week at
the end of the race.''
</P>
<P>
   MB2 Motorsports, which is owned by three Georgia residents, is
enjoying its best race weekend of the season. The team's drivers,
Johnny Benson and Ken Schrader, qualified second and eighth,
respectively. ``Kenny Schrader, (our two crew chiefs) and myself
have been doing a tremendous job of communicating back and forth,''
Johnny Benson said. ``We're getting our cars as equal as
possible.''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
